{"lemma":"كاذِبَةٍ","slug":"كاذِبَةٍ","root":"ك.ذ.ب","root_slug":"ك-ذ-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ذ-ب","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كاذِب","root":"كذب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":32},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36788"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%B0%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of كَذَبَ (kaḏaba): lying, untruthful","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"false, untrue","examples":[{"text":"بَلَاغٌ كَاذِبٌ","english":"false report"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"liar"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of كَذَبَ (kaḏaba, “to lie”)."},"ipa":["/kaː.ðib/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36788","headword_ar":"كَاذِبٌ","root":"k*b","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*~aAbN","text_ar":"كَذَّابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*uwbN","text_ar":"كَذُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ku*abapN","text_ar":"كُذَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*uwbapN","text_ar":"كَذُوبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiki*~aAbN","text_ar":"تِكِذَّابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiSid~aAqN","text_ar":"تِصِدَّاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*obaAnN","text_ar":"كَذْبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayo*ubaAnN","text_ar":"كَيْذُبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayo*abaAnN","text_ar":"كَيْذَبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mako*abaAnN","text_ar":"مَكْذَبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mako*abaAnapN","text_ar":"مَكْذَبَانَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ku*ubo*ubN","text_ar":"كُذُبْذُبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ku*~ubo*ubN","text_ar":"كُذُّبْذُبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K; neither of which last two words has its like in measure, IJ) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ku*ubo*ubaAnN","text_ar":"كُذُبْذُبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) epithets, applied to a man, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aba","text_ar":"كَذَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he lied, &c.: ” (S, K, &c.:) [the first word a simple epithet, signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lying, &c.;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a liar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"each of the others an intensive epithet, signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lying, &c., much; mendacious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habitual, liar"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. Pl. of the first word ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA*ibuwna","text_ar":"كَاذِبُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ku*~abN","text_ar":"كُذَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and of the third,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ku*ubN","text_ar":"كُذُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or, accord. to some, the last is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA*ibN","text_ar":"كَاذِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", contr. to analogy; or pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ki*aAbN","text_ar":"كِذَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is an inf. n. used as an intensive epithet. (MF.) ―         -b2-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*ibN","text_ar":"كَذِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASiyapK kaA*ibapK","text_ar":"نَاصِيَةٍ كَاذِبَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in the Kur xcvi. 16,] signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nASypK kA*bpK SaAHibuhaA","text_ar":"ناصيةٍ كاذبةٍ صَاحِبُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a forelock whose owner is a liar."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  Of the same kind is the expression ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^oyaA ka*uwbN","text_ar":"رُوْيَا كَذُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rw^yA SaAHibuhaA kaA*ibN","text_ar":"رويا صَاحِبُهَا كَاذِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dream whereof the dreamer finds it to be false,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a false,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain, dream"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See also a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayaAlN","text_ar":"خَيَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado yaSoduqu","text_ar":"قَدْ يَصْدُقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Alka*uwba","text_ar":"اـِنَّ الكَذُوبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the habitual liar in some few instances speaks truth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. A proverb. (TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA*ibN","text_ar":"كَاذِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muka*~ibN","text_ar":"مُكَذِّبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel that, being covered by the stallion, raises her tail, and then returns without conceiving."},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamolapN kaA*ibapN","text_ar":"حَمْلَةٌ كَاذِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mako*uwbapN","text_ar":"مَكْذُوبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahaA","text_ar":"لَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"? (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSoduwqapN","text_ar":"مَصْدُوقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A charge that is followed up with cowardice and retreating."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alka*~aAbaAni","text_ar":"الكَذَّابَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An epithet applied to Museylimeh El-Hanafee and El-Aswad El-'Ansee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [Each of them is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alk*~Ab","text_ar":"الكذّاب"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Az"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}